Commentary Text: Harshal Patel to Riyan Parag, SIX, what a finish to the innings. Riyan Parag has got RR to 144. On a short of length on off, not a bad ball at all, but Riyan Parag is standing deep and muscles the pull over deep mid-wicket. The ball again flies over the fence. Chahal runs off but there is some argy-bargy between Harshal Patel and Riyan Parag. And the broadcaster right on cue cuts to an ad -break. How apt! From what I saw, there was words exchanged between the bowler and batter, one of RR's subs puts his arm around Harshal to calm things before it all ended

Commentary Text: Hasaranga to Samson, out Bowled!! Oh dear! This is so daft from Samson, perhaps this is the story of his career. Looked million dollars and plays such a terrible shot to get himself dismissed, but Hasaranga and RCB will not care. Nicely tossed up around off, minimal spin, but it wasn't the length to play the standing reverse sweep, sneaks past the bat and flattens the off-pole. Commentary Text: Hazlewood to Buttler, out Caught by Siraj!! That's a ripper, and you needed one to get rid of Buttler - look at the celebrations in the RCB camp. It's once again Hazlewood with the wicket, banged in short and just outside off, Buttler was slightly cramped for room on the pull, hit it flat as he looked to roll his wrists over it, but Siraj was well in at mid-on, dives forward and pouches it with both hands, even as it was going down. Did so with soft hands and ensured he didn't spill as his elbow hit the turf. Buttler c Siraj b Hazlewood 8(9) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Siraj to Padikkal, out Lbw!! Padikkal has been given out LBW and he has reviewed it immediately. No bat and UltraEdge confirms it. Did it pitch outside leg? That's the only thing that can save Padikkal here. Onto ball-tracking: Taking a lot of time to build it up. It's pitching in line and it's crashing low into the middle-stump, three reds and Padikkal is OUT. This is shaping to be a good comeback after that first-ball six - full and at the stumps, Padikkal shuffled across on the flick and missed, pitched in line with leg and it straightened enough, to be crashing into the middle-stump, simple call for the umpire and Padikkal burns a review with him as well. Padikkal lbw b Siraj 7(7) [6s-1]

Commentary Text: Chahal to Shahbaz Ahmed, out Karthik Run Out!! Another run-out missed. Now, now. It's DK they've let go of. And it couldn't have been any easier. No. NO. Wait. DK is the one sleeping. He's the bigger culprit. And Yuzi Chahal, after messing up a simple return throw, doesn't believe what he's done. Through all that disappointment, he just picks the ball up and knocks the stumps. Karthik, after running half way down the pitch to a non-existent single, returns, and just gives up. He doesn't spot the misfield. He doesn't drag his bat in. Karthik run out (Prasidh/Chahal) 6(4) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Prasidh to Kohli, out Caught by Riyan Parag!! Another barely believable dismissal for Kohli. This is dug in short on the stumps, Kohli takes it on, toe-ends the pull and it lobs to backward point. Parag comes in to complete the catch. Kohli was through the shot too early and it went right off the bottom of the bat. Kohli walks off with a wry smile on his face again. Parag meanwhile does a jig. RR get the early wicket they wanted. Kohli c Riyan Parag b Prasidh 9(10) [4s-2]
